Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the
@penne pasta{180%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic
press{}). Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Grate the @mature cheddar
cheese{30%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.
When hot, add the @diced chicken breast{280%g} and cook until browned,
~{8-10%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Once browned, add the garlic,
@Italian style herbs{1%tsp}, @tomato puree{1%tbsp} and baby plum tomatoes and
cook for a further ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

Add the penne to the pan of boiling water and cook until tender,
~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan.
Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Add the @water{75%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g} to the pan with the
chicken. Bring to a boil, turn the heat down to simmer and cook for
~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until
wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once the spinach has wilted, stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g} and half
the Cheddar. Add the cooked pasta and season to taste with @salt{} and
@black pepper{}, then stir to combine.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Share the chicken pasta between your bowls and sprinkle over the remaining
Cheddar to finish. Enjoy!